title: Plants of Upper Coliban Reservoir, South Kyneton.
description: Indigenous species from around the Upper Coliban Reservoir area.

items.title: Eucalyptus radiata s.l.
items.content_text: Remnant forest of Narrow Leaved Peppermints.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: Need to have it identified. Some type of mullein I think.

items.title: Fungi spp.
items.content_text: Growing on decaying Silver wattle branch.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: This fungus grows out of cow manure.

items.title: Melicytus dentatus s.s.
items.content_text: Tree Violet. Only specimen in this area, that I know of.

items.title: Eucalyptus camaldulensis
items.content_text: River Red Gum. Not many left around here. Scattered in the paddocks and very old.

items.title: Arthropodium strictum s.s.
items.content_text: Chocolate Lily. There is another photo of a paler striped one.

items.title: Drosera peltata subsp. peltata spp. agg.
tags: id~Drosera peltata subsp. peltata spp. agg.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: Lomandra species. Not sure which one?South Kyneton.

items.title: Lythrum salicaria
items.content_text: Found at bottom of Upper Coliban Reservoir when it was dry. Possibly a garden escapee?

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: Some wetland ground cover. Not sure which species. Found at bottom of Upper Coliban reservoir when it was empty a few years back.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: Indigenous Snow Gums on the property.There are about ten of them. New ones have been planted to preserve them.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: A specimen of a snow gum.

items.title: Eucalyptus pauciflora
items.content_text: A small stand of Snow Gum's near the reservoir. There are not many of these around this area. A few scattered trees on the Kyneton side of the reservoir and a few stands on the Tylden side.

items.title: Pimelea humilis
items.content_text: Growing around rocks in the fenced off remnant vegetation area. Small groundcover about 10cm high and spreading to about 20cm.

items.title: Themeda triandra
items.content_text: Kangaroo Grass flourishing after I fenced off remnant vegetation in paddock.

items.title: Unidentified
items.content_text: Tall Bluebell.Also found in fenced off remnant vegetation area.

items.title: Pelargonium rodneyanum
items.content_text: Geranium that is found in the rocky area in the paddock, fenced off area.I think it is geranium rodneyii.
